17 (1) 'Department' means the Department of Public Health.
18 (2) 'Emergency' means a condition or set of circumstances demanding immediate
19 attention to prevent death or substantial and irreversible physical impairment of a major
20 bodily function.
21 (3) 'Healthcare professional' means a physician, nurse, or other healthcare practitioner
22 licensed, registered, or certified by the state to provide healthcare services consistent with
23 his or her scope of practice.
24 (4) 'Healthcare services' means services for the diagnosis, prevention, treatment, cure,
25 or relief of a physical health condition, illness, injury, or disease.
26 (5) 'Hotline service' means the Infant Wellness Resource hotline service established
27 pursuant to this Code section.
28 (6) 'Infant' means a child under three years of age.
29 (7) 'Telehealth' means the use of electronic information and telecommunications
30 technologies that include, at minimum, audio and video equipment permitting two-way,
31 real-time interactive communication to support and promote long-distance healthcare
32 services between a caller and a healthcare professional.
33 (b) Subject to available funding, the department shall establish and maintain, on a 24 hour
34 per day basis, an Infant Wellness Resource hotline service, which shall receive and respond
35 to calls from persons who are seeking help for an infant who is experiencing a health issue
36 or illness, in accordance with subsection (c) of this Code section, and for any other purpose
37 provided for in this Code section.
38 (c) Upon receipt of a call, hotline service staff shall promptly identify whether the call is
39 an emergency. If hotline service staff deem that the call:
40 (1) Is not an emergency, such staff shall either refer or directly connect the caller to
41 appropriate state and local programs, healthcare services, healthcare professionals, and
42 other resources that can be accessed by the caller and used to address, mitigate, and
43 potentially eliminate the health issue or illness. Referrals and connections made pursuant
