44 to this paragraph may be facilitated through the use of telephone or digital
45 communications, including, but not limited to, text message, email, or online support
46 chat. Hotline service staff shall not provide direct healthcare services. Callers referred
47 for healthcare services under this paragraph shall be provided the opportunity to consult
48 with an authorized healthcare professional via telehealth within two business days; or
49 (2) Is an emergency, such staff shall immediately effectuate a warm hand-off of the
50 caller to staff at 9-1-1 emergency services. A warm hand-off performed under this
51 paragraph shall involve hotline service staff using teleconferencing technology to transfer
52 the call; remaining on the line and accessible to the caller during the transfer of the call;
53 formally introducing the caller to the staff member receiving the call at 9-1-1 emergency
54 services; and summarizing, for such receiving staff member, the information that
55 necessitated the transfer of the call. At no time during a warm hand-off conducted
56 pursuant to this paragraph shall a caller be placed on hold.
57 (d) The Department of Administrative Services shall, in coordination with the department,
58 select and contract with ten or more healthcare providers, as it deems necessary, to provide
59 healthcare services via telehealth pursuant to this Code section. All healthcare services
60 provided pursuant to such contracts shall be provided by healthcare professionals licensed
61 to provide such services under the laws of this state. The factors used to select such
62 healthcare professionals shall include, but shall not be limited to:
63 (1) A demonstrated ability to maximize payment for healthcare services from
64 commercial insurers and other third parties;
65 (2) The ability to provide healthcare services in a language fluently spoken by the callers
66 receiving such services;
67 (3) A demonstrated record of providing healthcare services via telehealth to infants;
68 (4) The ability to use information technology to track healthcare services provided and
69 outcomes for program evaluation purposes; and
